{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "For prompt-based attacks, manual prompts are often more effective than automated prompt-based attack methods.",
    "As automated attack methods are primarily designed for generalized tasks, they may not demonstrate same effectiveness for specific tasks as manually crafted prompts.",
    "The unlabeled and imbalanced realworld data further complicate the development of effective automated prompting-based attack methods [238].",
    "For backdoor attacks, most of them are focused on classification or similar tasks [21], e.g., sentiment analysis and opinion classification.",
    "More attention should be paid to the attacks that perform other NLP tasks, including question answering, text summarization, and language translation."
  ],
